<collection><source>GO_Annotation</source><date>20130316</date><key>go_annotation.key</key><document><id>21127054</id><passage><infon key="type">abstract</infon><offset>102</offset><annotation id="21127054_1"><infon key="gene">Pik3c2a(361632)</infon><infon key="go-term">positive regulation of insulin secretion|GO:0032024</infon><infon key="goevidence">IMP</infon><infon key="type">GOA</infon><location offset="412" length="309"/><text>Here we show that down-regulation of the class II PI3K isoform PI3K-C2alpha specifically impairs insulin granule exocytosis in rat insulinoma cells without affecting insulin content, the number of insulin granules at the plasma membrane, or the expression levels of key proteins involved in insulin secretion.</text></annotation></passage><passage><infon key="type">title_4</infon><offset>19086</offset><annotation id="21127054_2"><infon key="gene">Pik3c2a(361632)</infon><infon key="go-term">regulation of insulin secretion|GO:0050796</infon><infon key="goevidence">IMP</infon><infon key="type">GOA</infon><location offset="19086" length="49"/><text>PI3K-C2alpha Regulates Insulin Granule Exocytosis</text></annotation></passage><passage><infon key="type">paragraph</infon><offset>19136</offset><annotation id="21127054_3"><infon key="gene">Pik3c2a(361632)</infon><infon key="go-term">positive regulation of insulin secretion|GO:0032024</infon><infon key="goevidence">IMP</infon><infon key="type">GOA</infon><location offset="19662" length="222"/><text>Consistent with this hypothesis, we observed that down-regulation of PI3K-C2alpha strongly reduced the total amount of insulin secreted upon cellular stimulation in both PI3K-C2alpha knockdown cell lines (Fig. 2, B and C).</text></annotation><annotation id="21127054_4"><infon key="gene">Pik3c2a(361632)</infon><infon key="go-term">regulation of insulin secretion|GO:0050796</infon><infon key="goevidence">NONE</infon><infon key="type">GOA</infon><location offset="20840" length="107"/><text>Taken together, these data indicate that PI3K-C2alpha specifically regulates secretion of insulin granules.</text></annotation></passage></document></collection>
